Parliament, Tuesday, 23 June 2020 – The Portfolio Committee on Communications will this evening hold a three-hour virtual meeting, from 18:00 to 21:00, to be briefed by the Independent Communications Authority of South Africa (Icasa) on various regulations that are before Icasa, as well as licensing of the International Mobile Telecommunications spectrum, regulation of Television white spaces and, licensing of the Wireless Open Access Network.
	
	Members of the media who would like to be part of the meetings to observe may forward their contact details to Mr Mlindi Mpindi on 081 716 7329 for inclusion in the Parliament Communications Service WhatsApp group, where login details will be shared.
	
	Members of the public may get involved and follow committee sittings live on Parliament TV (DStv Channel 408), via live stream on Parliament YouTube channel and Twitter page on the links below. You may subscribe to the Parliament YouTube channel to receive instant notification of live feeds.
	
	Twitter: https://twitter.com/ParliamentofRSA
	Facebook: https://facebook.com/ParliamentofRSA
	 YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/ParliamentofRSA
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES
	
